Package net.ssehub.comani.data

Class CommitSerializer

java.lang.Object
net.ssehub.comani.data.CommitSerializer
public class CommitSerializer
extends java.lang.Object
This class provides capabilities to save individual Commit objects as CDMS-files and to read such files for creating Commit objects based on their CDMS-elements. CDMS stands for ComAnI Data Model Serialization, which is a built-in format for caching extracted commits.
Author:
Christian Kroeher

    • serialize

      public static boolean serialize​(Commit commit, java.io.File targetDirectory)
      Saves the given Commit as CDMS-file to the given directory.
      Parameters:
      commit - the commit to save; should never be null
      targetDirectory - the directory for saving the CDMS-file to; should always exist and be empty
      Returns:
      true if saving the commit was successful; false otherwise

    • deserialize

      public static boolean deserialize​(Commit commit, java.io.File commitCdmsFile)
      Adds the information of the given CDMS-file to the given Commit.
      Parameters:
      commit - a commit to which the information of the given CDMS-file will be added; should never be null
      commitCdmsFile - the CDMS-file containing the information, which will be added to the commit; should never be null
      Returns:
      true if the information of the CDMS-file was added to the commit successfully; false otherwise
